When an online game turns real, trapping its players in its virtual space, the strongest of them, Shin, rises up to put a stop to the madness. But just moments after defeating the games final boss, Origin, and freeing everyone, Shin is transported 500 years into the future of the in-game world. Armed with unrivaled strength, the young swordsman embarks on a legendary journey.
(Source: Crunchyroll)
Genjitsu Shugi Yuusha no Oukoku Saikenki

Suddenly summoned to a fantasy world and betrothed to the princess, Kazuya Souma is crowned the new king after providing the royal family with impressive advice. To rule the kingdom, he's taking the nontraditional (and very human) route of administrative reform. In a realm of dragons and elves, will this revolutionary's unique path prove effective?
(Source: Funimation)

Cyan Vert, illegitimate son of the Duke and the empire's greatest assassin, is betrayed by the righteous brother whose shadow he's always lived in. But just before the fatal blow strikes his throat, Cyan awakes to find he's just a boy again. The young lord has been reborn, and this time, he's not going to live in anyone's shadow!
(Source: WEBTOONS)
(Kono Sekai wa Mou Ore ga Sukutte Tomi to Kenryoku wo Te ni Iretashi, Onna Kishi ya Onna Maou to Shiro de Tanoshiku Kurashiteru kara, Ore Igai no Yuusha wa) Mou Isekai ni Konaide Kudasai.

[Question] A new different world hero appeared on Horizon [Answer] Turn back to Earth right now!
After the struggle, I saved the other world and tried to enjoy the rest of my life freely. But for some reason, the incarnating hero from the earth will spring up here on the Horizon. Don't be silly! This world is mine!
The Holy Knight, the Demon Girl, the Elves, the Beastmen, and even the ordinary people, everything in this world will never be given to anyone!
NEET? Izakaya? SDF? No matter who the enemy is! Other-hero, turn back to the Earth!
Drive back all the other world hero with wisdom, courage and perfection, a slapstick fantasy opens!
(Source: Kadokawa, translated)
